  "summary": "After a loud knocking at the door, Inspector Batter opens it to a crowd of people rushing into the library. They find Jimmy Sycamore lying limp on the ground amidst broken items. Sycamore regains consciousness and explains that he fought a strong thief who attempted to escape through a window by climbing down the ivy. Sycamore reveals that he fired his \"Leopold\" blued-barrel automatic pistol once at the intruder, but the thief managed to fire back at him before escaping.\n\nSir Stanley Digby discovers that Terence O'Rourke was likely drugged and that important documents have been stolen. While George Lomax initially fears the files are lost, Batter reveals that Loren Wade has recovered a brown paper package containing the missing items. Sir Stanley and Herr Eberhard inspect the package and confirm its contents.\n\nAs George Lomax instructs Bill Everly to call Dr. Carterright to attend to O'Rourke, George, Sir Stanley, and Rupert Betman leave the room to take further measures. Superintendent Bartlett observes the group and wonders about the whereabouts of Osborne Kutt. The group is interrupted by the arrival of Sir Oswald, who appears at the window. Sir Oswald presents a small Mauser pistol he found on the lawn, suggesting it was dropped by the thief. Batter places the Mauser on the table next to Sycamore's pistol. Sir Oswald requests an explanation of the events, and Detective Bartholomew briefly recounts the situation.",
